@pranavsharma Exact same issue with .NET SDK style projects and any other .net project using [`PackageReference`-style](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/nuget/consume-packages/package-references-in-project-files) project files!
Issue is in file `\build\netstandard1.1\Microsoft.ML.OnnxRuntime.Gpu.props`, I belief: 
```
  <ItemGroup Condition="Exists('packages.config') OR
                        Exists('$(MSBuildProjectName).packages.config') OR
                        Exists('packages.$(MSBuildProjectName).config')">
```
I'm not sure why you would need any condition here anyway.
It's definitely a bug in your nuget package.

issue.body:
**Description**: Removed obsolete condition in nuget package props file.

**Motivation and Context**
- This change is required to allow nuget package consumption on any project file using `PackageReference`s (including .net sdk-style projects)
- Resolves issue #3101
- Resolves issue #116 (which was closed without solving the underlying issue)
